FOSSIL MATERIAL: BMNH PAL 5922 (
fig. 1A–C
), an incomplete skeleton consisting of skull (
fig. 1A
), incomplete rostral portion of mandible, pterygoid, atlas, axis, thoracic and caudal vertebrae, complete furcula (
fig. 1B
), left and right coracoids (
fig. 1C
), left and right scapulae, incomplete sternum (lacking posterior portions), incomplete anterior por­ tion of pelvis, complete right and incomplete left humeri, distal ends of left radius and ulna, left ulnare, complete left carpometacarpus, complete phalanges, and minor digits of left forearm. For complete description and illustration of this material, see Olson (
1999
).
